#NAME#
.PP
SecureSdb - Create a SecureSdb object.
.PP
#SYNOPSIS#
.PP
\f[B]\f[BI]new SecureSdb( [hostname], [svcname] )\f[B]\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]\f[BI]var securesdb = new SecureSdb( [hostname], [svcname], [username],
[password] )\f[B]\f[R]
.PP
#CATEGORY#
.PP
SecureSdb
.PP
#DESCRIPTION#
.PP
Create a SecureSdb object.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R]
.RE
.RS
.IP "1." 3
SecureSdb is subclass of Sdb and SecureSdb object uses SSL connection.
.RE
.RS
.IP "2." 3
The method and syntax of the SecureSdb object and the Sdb object are the same.
.RE
.PP
